info.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 12 at 2:59AM EST until February 12 at 6:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM EST /5 PM CST/ THIS EVENING... * WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph this morning with gusts up to 50 mph, decreasing this afternoon to 20 to 25 mph with gusts up to 40 mph. * WHERE...Exposed coastal locations, including South Walton, Coastal Bay, Coastal Gulf, Coastal Franklin, Coastal Taylor and Coastal Dixie Counties. * WHEN...Until 6 PM EST /5 PM CST/ Sunday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: A Wind Advisory means that sustained winds of 26 to 39 mph are expected for at least 2 hours, or gusts between 40 to 57 mph for any length of time are possible.Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
